  ---URL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/spring-cloud/spring-cloud-stream/v5.0.1/docs/modules/ROOT/pages/kafka/kafka-binder/usage.adoc
  = Usage
  
  To use Apache Kafka binder, you need to add `spring-cloud-stream-binder-kafka` as a dependency to your Spring Cloud Stream application, as shown in the following example for Maven:
  
  [source,xml]
  ----
  <dependency>
    <groupId>org.springframework.cloud</groupId>
    <artifactId>spring-cloud-stream-binder-kafka</artifactId>
  </dependency>
  ----
  
  Alternatively, you can also use the Spring Cloud Stream Kafka Starter, as shown in the following example for Maven:
  
  [source,xml]
  ----
  <dependency>
    <groupId>org.springframework.cloud</groupId>
    <artifactId>spring-cloud-starter-stream-kafka</artifactId>
  </dependency>
  ----
  
  
  ---URL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/spring-cloud/spring-cloud-stream/main/docs/modules/ROOT/pages/kafka/kafka-binder/usage.adoc
